<li id="cite_note-55">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="I#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The compiler could not tell whether a statement was a declaration or a multiple assignment statement until encountering the "=" of the assignment or ";" of the DECLARE - which could be several lines later. The fact that DECLARE/DCL were not reserved is the proximate cause in this example - consider the fragment <code>DECLARE(I,J,K),L=</code> vs <code>DECLARE(I,J,K),L;</code>.</span>
</li>
